outputs.description: Social Protection Forum is formed and dialogue initiated on options for a social protection system

The budget observatory platform has capacities to advocate, analyze and monitor public expenditures in the social sectors andkey ministries', decentralized levels and national assembly member's skills are upgraded to design, approve and implement childfriendly and equity- focused policies and legislative measures.
Print and broadcasting media have capacities to effectively analyze and popularized the equity agenda, child rights and protectionissues.
The MoBSE staffs have capacities to plan, implement, monitor and report on disaster risk reduction and response in Education.
By 2016, 600 communities are committed to abandonment of open defecation and have implemented CLTS action plan.
75% of care givers in the 20 targeted districts have functional knowledge and skills in the 4+ 2 key Household practices and areempowered to practice them by 2016.
Effective and Efficient Programme delivery, supply and procurement
By 2016, 200 Lower Basic Schools in 20 targeted districts implement the PIQSS package, including ECD.

By 2016, an in service Teacher training system is operational and the pre-service curriculum at the Gambia College and thePrimary Teachers Extension Training Programme includes child centered and ECD modules.
Implementation of national education strategic plans and policies informed by equity focused research including inclusive educationfor children with disability.
By 2016, a comprehensive child protection system developed and functional.
By 2016, core child protection services available and communities empowered to respond to child protection issues, especially inthe targeted districts
By 2013, DSW/Min. of Children affairs at central and regional levels have capacities to plan, implement, monitor and report onchild protection services including during emergencies.
By 2016, a revitalized PHC strategy operational in the 20 targeted districts.
Comprehensive package  of high impact health and nutrition interventions delivered in the 20 targeted districts by 2016.
Universal immunization  for immunizations, Deworming and VAS by 2016.
DRR strategies in place and 100% of children and women affected by disaster supported timely with supplies, diseases preventionand treatment interventions.
WASH services delivered, utilized and maintained in 200 PIQSS schools and selected communities  in the 20 targeted districts.
By 2016, equity based quality data is available and used for advocacy, designing, implementation, monitoring and reporting ofnational programmes, policies and laws.
By 2016, Key Social Sectors including the regional offices have enhanced capacities in Programme planning, monitoring andevaluation.
By 2016, acceptance of domestic violence and FGM/C at the national level decreased by 25 and 22.5 percentage points respectively
By 2016, 100% of communities participating in the community empowerment programme are committed to abandon FGM/C, child marriage,violence against children and declare it in a public declaration.
